<div class="footnotes">
  <div class="footnote-card">
    <h3>🔵 Why Microsoft Dynamics 365?</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>HUD already uses Microsoft infrastructure (M365, Teams)</li>
      <li>FedRAMP authorized for government data</li>
      <li>Native integration with Power Platform, Copilot Studio, Azure AI</li>
      <li>Case management, workflows, and dashboards built-in</li>
      <li>Strong audit trail and compliance features (Purview)</li>
      <li>No vendor lock-in on AI layer — plugs into Claude, Azure OpenAI, GPT-4o</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="footnote-card">
    <h3>🟠 Why Claude as Primary AI?</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Document reasoning:</strong> Best-in-class for long legal docs, leases, case files</li>
      <li><strong>Low hallucination:</strong> Critical for legal/compliance accuracy</li>
      <li><strong>Nuanced language:</strong> Detects subtle discriminatory language patterns</li>
      <li><strong>Instruction-following:</strong> Strict adherence to FHA policy rules</li>
      <li><strong>Perplexity:</strong> Best for live web research on regulations & case law</li>
      <li><strong>Azure OpenAI (GPT-4o):</strong> Translation, embeddings, classification tasks</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="footnote-card">
    <h3>📅 Recommended Rollout Phases</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Phase 1 (Months 1–6):</strong> Intake, Triage, Public Education, Stakeholder Notifications, Workflow Orchestration</li>
      <li><strong>Phase 2 (Months 7–12):</strong> Document Review, Case Research, Conciliation, Dashboard, Investigator Assist</li>
      <li><strong>Phase 3 (Months 13–18):</strong> Pattern Detection, Advertising Audit, Algorithmic Bias, Zoning Monitor</li>
      <li><strong>Phase 4 (Months 18–24):</strong> Congressional Reporting, FOIA, Data Security & Privacy</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

